  <title>hydrogen bond</title>
  <termversion>2.3.3</termversion>
  <lastupdated>2014-02-24</lastupdated>
  <definitions>
    <item>
      <id>1</id>
      <text>A form of association between an electronegative atom and a hydrogen atom attached to a second, relatively electronegative atom. It is best considered as an electrostatic interaction, heightened by the small size of hydrogen, which permits proximity of the interacting dipoles or charges. Both electronegative atoms are usually (but not necessarily) from the first row of the Periodic Table, i.e. N, O or F. Hydrogen bonds may be inter-molecular or intramolecular. With a few exceptions, usually involving fluorine, the associated energies are less than 20-25 kJ mol-1 - 5-6 kcal mol-1 ( - ).</text>
